WEBVTT

1
00:02:08.160 --> 00:02:09.480
Welcome. Lord Stark.

2
00:02:09.640 --> 00:02:12.480
Grand Maester Pycelle has called
a meeting of the Small Council.

3
00:02:12.640 --> 00:02:14.360
The honor of your presence is requested.

4
00:02:16.320 --> 00:02:18.920
Get the girls settled in. 
I'll be back in time for supper.

5
00:02:19.080 --> 00:02:21.520
-And. Jory. you go with them. 
-Yes. my lord.

6
00:02:21.680 --> 00:02:25.800
If you'd like to change
into something more appropriate...

7
00:02:35.160 --> 00:02:37.280
(DOORS CREAKING)

8
00:02:59.880 --> 00:03:01.880
Thank the gods you're here. Stark.

9
00:03:03.120 --> 00:03:07.040
About time we had
some stern Northern leadership.

10
00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:08.800
Glad to see
you're protecting the throne.

11
00:03:08.960 --> 00:03:10.960
Sturdy old thing.

12
00:03:11.120 --> 00:03:13.080
How many kings' asses
have polished it. I wonder?

13
00:03:13.240 --> 00:03:15.040
Um. what's the line?

14
00:03:15.200 --> 00:03:18.120
The king shits and the Hand wipes.

15
00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:21.520
Very handsome armor.

16
00:03:21.680 --> 00:03:24.320
-Not a scratch on it.
-I know.

17
00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:27.360
People have been swinging at me
for years. but they always seem to miss.

18
00:03:27.520 --> 00:03:29.920
You've chosen your opponents
wisely then.

19
00:03:31.360 --> 00:03:33.080
I have a knack for it.

20
00:03:36.400 --> 00:03:40.240
It must be strange for you
coming into this room.

21
00:03:41.600 --> 00:03:45.120
I was standing right here
when it happened.

22
00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:47.080
He was very brave. your brother.

23
00:03:47.240 --> 00:03:49.160
Your father too.

24
00:03:49.320 --> 00:03:51.040
They didn't deserve to die like that.

25
00:03:51.200 --> 00:03:54.040
Nobody deserves to die like that.

26
00:03:54.200 --> 00:03:55.680
But you just stood there and watched.

27
00:03:55.840 --> 00:03:59.520
500 men just stood there and watched.

28
00:03:59.680 --> 00:04:01.160
All the great knights
of the Seven Kingdoms--

29
00:04:01.320 --> 00:04:04.680
you think anyone said a word.
lifted a finger?

30
00:04:04.840 --> 00:04:06.800
No. lord Stark.

31
00:04:06.960 --> 00:04:11.120
500 men
and this room was silent as a crypt.

32
00:04:12.280 --> 00:04:15.280
Except for the screams. of course.

33
00:04:15.440 --> 00:04:17.160
and the Mad King laughing.

34
00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:20.000
And later...

35
00:04:20.160 --> 00:04:22.400
When I watched the Mad King die.

36
00:04:22.560 --> 00:04:27.000
I remembered him laughing
as your father burned...

37
00:04:27.160 --> 00:04:29.280
It felt like justice.

38
00:04:31.760 --> 00:04:34.960
Is that what you tell yourself at night?

39
00:04:35.120 --> 00:04:37.680
You're a servant of justice?

40
00:04:37.840 --> 00:04:39.760
That you were avenging my father
when you shoved your sword

41
00:04:39.920 --> 00:04:42.360
in Aerys Targaryen's back?

42
00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:43.920
Tell me--

43
00:04:44.080 --> 00:04:47.040
if I'd stabbed the Mad King in the belly
instead of the back.

44
00:04:47.200 --> 00:04:49.720
would you admire me more?

45
00:04:49.880 --> 00:04:52.040
You served him well

46
00:04:52.200 --> 00:04:55.160
when serving was safe.

47
00:05:06.080 --> 00:05:07.960
Lord Stark.

48
00:05:10.760 --> 00:05:13.120
-Lord Varys.
-I was grievously sorry

49
00:05:13.280 --> 00:05:15.680
to hear of your troubles
on the Kingsroad.

50
00:05:15.840 --> 00:05:19.080
We are all praying
for prince Joffrey's full recovery.

51
00:05:19.240 --> 00:05:22.200
A shame you didn't say a prayer
for the butcher's son.

52
00:05:23.560 --> 00:05:26.840
Renly! You're looking well.

53
00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:28.360
And you look tired from the road.

54
00:05:28.520 --> 00:05:30.560
I told them this meeting could wait
another day. but--

55
00:05:30.720 --> 00:05:33.120
MAN: But we have a kingdom
to look after.

56
00:05:34.240 --> 00:05:36.280
I've hoped to meet you for some time.
Lord Stark.

57
00:05:36.440 --> 00:05:40.560
-No doubt Lady Catelyn has mentioned me.
-She has. Lord Baelish.

58
00:05:40.720 --> 00:05:42.920
I understand you knew
my brother Brandon as well.

59
00:05:43.080 --> 00:05:46.040
All too well.
I still carry a token of his esteem

60
00:05:46.200 --> 00:05:47.800
from navel to collarbone.

61
00:05:47.960 --> 00:05:49.920
Perhaps you chose the wrong man
to duel with.

62
00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:52.120
It wasn't the man that I chose. my lord.

63
00:05:52.280 --> 00:05:54.160
It was Catelyn Tully.

64
00:05:54.320 --> 00:05:57.280
A woman worth fighting for.
I'm sure you'll agree.

65
00:05:57.440 --> 00:06:00.680
I humbly beg your pardon. my lord Stark.

66
00:06:00.840 --> 00:06:02.560
Grand Maester.

67
00:06:02.720 --> 00:06:04.640
How many years has it been?

68
00:06:04.800 --> 00:06:08.000
-You were a young man.
-And you served another king.

69
00:06:10.040 --> 00:06:14.080
Oh. how forgetful of me.
(MUMBLING)

70
00:06:14.240 --> 00:06:17.160
This belongs to you. now.

71
00:06:18.880 --> 00:06:20.280
Should we begin?

72
00:06:21.640 --> 00:06:23.400
-Without the king?
-Winter may be coming.

73
00:06:23.560 --> 00:06:26.440
but I'm afraid the same cannot be said
for my brother.

74
00:06:26.600 --> 00:06:28.600
VARYS: His grace has many cares.

75
00:06:28.760 --> 00:06:31.560
He entrusts some small matters to us

76
00:06:31.720 --> 00:06:33.240
that we might lighten the load.

77
00:06:33.400 --> 00:06:35.920
We are the lords of small matters here.

78
00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:41.320
(CLEARS THROAT)

79
00:06:41.480 --> 00:06:43.640
My brother instructs us
to stage a tournament

80
00:06:43.800 --> 00:06:45.920
in honor of Lord Stark's appointment
as Hand of the King.

81
00:06:46.080 --> 00:06:49.520
-Mmm. how much?
-40.000 gold dragons to the champion.

82
00:06:49.680 --> 00:06:54.120
20.000 to the runner-up.
20.000 to the winning archer.

83
00:06:54.280 --> 00:06:56.480
Can the treasury bear such expense?

84
00:06:56.640 --> 00:06:59.200
I'll have to borrow it. The Lannisters
will accommodate. I expect.

85
00:06:59.360 --> 00:07:02.480
We already owe Lord Tywin three million
gold. What's another 80.000?

86
00:07:02.640 --> 00:07:04.320
Are you telling me the crown
is three million in debt?

87
00:07:04.480 --> 00:07:06.240
I'm telling you the crown
is six million in debt.

88
00:07:06.400 --> 00:07:08.160
How could you let this happen?

89
00:07:08.320 --> 00:07:09.840
The Master of Coin finds the money.

90
00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:12.200
The king and the Hand spend it.

91
00:07:12.360 --> 00:07:15.280
I will not believe Jon Arryn
allowed Robert to bankrupt the realm.

92
00:07:15.440 --> 00:07:18.960
Lord Arryn gave wise and prudent advice.

93
00:07:19.120 --> 00:07:22.200
but I fear his grace
doesn't always listen.

94
00:07:22.360 --> 00:07:24.520
"Counting coppers." he calls it.

95
00:07:25.520 --> 00:07:27.440
I'll speak to him tomorrow.

96
00:07:27.600 --> 00:07:29.640
This tournament is an extravagance
we cannot afford.

97
00:07:29.800 --> 00:07:32.360
As you will.
But still. we'd best make our plans.

98
00:07:32.520 --> 00:07:34.000
There will be no plans

99
00:07:34.160 --> 00:07:36.080
until I speak to Robert.

100
00:07:39.760 --> 00:07:41.720
Forgive me. my lords. I'm--

101
00:07:41.880 --> 00:07:43.720
I had a long ride.

102
00:07:43.880 --> 00:07:48.960
You are the King's Hand. Lord Stark.
we serve at your pleasure.

103
00:07:55.640 --> 00:07:58.560
-Ow!
-Please. it's nearly healed.

104
00:07:59.800 --> 00:08:03.040
-It's ugly.
-A king should have scars.

105
00:08:03.200 --> 00:08:06.440
You fought off a dire wolf.
You're a warrior like your father.

106
00:08:06.600 --> 00:08:08.800
I'm not like him.
I didn't fight off anything.

107
00:08:08.960 --> 00:08:10.920
It bit me and all I did was scream.

108
00:08:11.080 --> 00:08:12.800
And the two Stark girls saw it.
both of them.

109
00:08:12.960 --> 00:08:16.120
That's not true. You killed the beast.

110
00:08:16.280 --> 00:08:19.120
You only spared the girl because of
the love your father bears her father.

111
00:08:19.280 --> 00:08:21.040
-I didn't. I--
-When Aerys Targaryen sat

112
00:08:21.200 --> 00:08:25.200
on the Iron Throne.
your father was a rebel and a traitor.

113
00:08:25.360 --> 00:08:29.920
Someday you'll sit on the throne
and the truth will be what you make it.

114
00:08:32.280 --> 00:08:34.080
Do I have to marry her?

115
00:08:35.080 --> 00:08:36.800
Yes.

116
00:08:36.960 --> 00:08:39.000
She's very beautiful and young.

117
00:08:39.160 --> 00:08:42.160
If you don't like her. you only need
to see her on formal occasions

118
00:08:42.320 --> 00:08:46.280
and when the time comes.
to make little princes and princesses.

119
00:08:47.640 --> 00:08:51.440
And if you'd rather fuck painted whores.
you'll fuck painted whores.

120
00:08:51.600 --> 00:08:53.880
And if you'd rather lie
with noble virgins. so be it.

121
00:08:54.040 --> 00:08:55.720
You are my darling boy
and the world will be

122
00:08:55.880 --> 00:08:57.880
exactly as you want it to be.

123
00:09:01.360 --> 00:09:03.640
Do something nice for the Stark girl.

124
00:09:03.800 --> 00:09:06.360
-I don't want to.
-No. but you will.

125
00:09:06.520 --> 00:09:10.360
The occasional kindness will spare you
all sorts of trouble down the road.

126
00:09:10.520 --> 00:09:12.800
We allow the northerners too much power.

127
00:09:12.960 --> 00:09:15.400
They consider themselves our equals.

128
00:09:15.560 --> 00:09:17.640
How would you handle them?

129
00:09:17.800 --> 00:09:19.680
I'd double their taxes

130
00:09:19.840 --> 00:09:22.280
and command them
to supply 10.000 men to the royal army.

131
00:09:22.440 --> 00:09:24.200
-A royal army?
-Why should every lord

132
00:09:24.360 --> 00:09:27.480
command his own men? It's primitive.
no better than the hill tribes.

133
00:09:27.640 --> 00:09:30.680
We should have a standing army
of men loyal to the crown.

134
00:09:30.840 --> 00:09:33.920
trained by experienced soldiers--
instead of a mob of peasants

135
00:09:34.080 --> 00:09:36.880
who've never held pikes in their lives.

136
00:09:37.040 --> 00:09:39.960
-And if the Northerners rebel?
-I'd crush them.

137
00:09:40.120 --> 00:09:42.680
Seize Winterfell
and install someone loyal to the realm

138
00:09:42.840 --> 00:09:45.400
as Warden of the North.
Uncle Kevan. maybe.

139
00:09:45.560 --> 00:09:49.040
And these 10.000 northern troops.
would they fight for you or their lord?

140
00:09:49.200 --> 00:09:51.480
-For me. I'm their king.
-Mm-hmm.

141
00:09:51.640 --> 00:09:53.200
But you've just invaded their homeland.

142
00:09:53.360 --> 00:09:56.000
-asked them to kill their brothers.
-I'm not asking.

143
00:09:56.160 --> 00:09:58.960
The North cannot be held--
not by an outsider.

144
00:09:59.120 --> 00:10:01.520
It's too big and too wild.
And when the winter comes.

145
00:10:01.680 --> 00:10:05.040
the Seven Gods together couldn't
save you and your royal army.

146
00:10:05.200 --> 00:10:08.000
A good king knows
when to save his strength...

147
00:10:09.360 --> 00:10:11.280
and when to destroy his enemies.

148
00:10:12.720 --> 00:10:14.640
So you agree...

149
00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:17.000
The Starks are enemies?

150
00:10:18.520 --> 00:10:20.880
Everyone who isn't us

151
00:10:21.040 --> 00:10:23.080
is an enemy.

152
00:10:25.200 --> 00:10:27.320
Enough of that. young lady.
Eat your food.

153
00:10:27.480 --> 00:10:29.360
-I'm practicing.
-Practicing for what?

154
00:10:29.520 --> 00:10:31.360
-The prince.
-Arya. stop!

155
00:10:31.520 --> 00:10:33.240
He's a liar and a coward

156
00:10:33.400 --> 00:10:35.760
-and he killed my friend.
-The Hound killed your friend.

157
00:10:35.920 --> 00:10:38.280
The Hound does
whatever the prince tells him to do.

158
00:10:38.440 --> 00:10:40.760
-You're an idiot.
-You're a liar. If you told the truth

159
00:10:40.920 --> 00:10:43.200
-Mycah would be alive.
-Enough!

160
00:10:45.920 --> 00:10:47.240
What's happening here?

161
00:10:47.400 --> 00:10:50.800
Arya would rather act like a beast
than a lady.

162
00:10:50.960 --> 00:10:53.440
Go to your room. We'll speak later.

163
00:11:01.120 --> 00:11:03.760
That's for you. love.

164
00:11:12.120 --> 00:11:15.200
The same dollmaker makes
all of princess Myrcella's toys.

165
00:11:17.680 --> 00:11:19.400
Don't you like it?

166
00:11:19.560 --> 00:11:22.040
I haven't played with dolls
since I was eight.

167
00:11:23.560 --> 00:11:26.320
-May I be excused?
-You've barely eaten a thing.

168
00:11:27.640 --> 00:11:30.440
It's all right. Go on.

169
00:11:38.880 --> 00:11:40.760
War was easier than daughters.

170
00:11:45.320 --> 00:11:47.760
(KNOCKS)
Go away!

171
00:11:47.920 --> 00:11:50.240
NED: Arya. open the door.

172
00:11:59.520 --> 00:12:01.320
May I come in?

173
00:12:07.840 --> 00:12:10.320
-Whose sword is that?
-Mine.

174
00:12:10.480 --> 00:12:12.280
Give it to me.

175
00:12:18.800 --> 00:12:21.640
I know this maker's mark.
This is Mikken's work.

176
00:12:23.640 --> 00:12:25.360
Where did you get this?

177
00:12:28.960 --> 00:12:31.120
This is no toy.

178
00:12:33.000 --> 00:12:35.800
-Ladies shouldn't play with swords.
-I wasn't playing.

179
00:12:35.960 --> 00:12:38.320
And I don't want to be a lady.

180
00:12:38.480 --> 00:12:40.280
Come here.

181
00:12:45.200 --> 00:12:47.080
Now what do you want with this?

182
00:12:47.240 --> 00:12:49.320
It's called Needle.

183
00:12:49.480 --> 00:12:52.640
Oh. a blade with a name.

184
00:12:52.800 --> 00:12:55.000
And who were you hoping to skewer
with Needle?

185
00:12:55.160 --> 00:12:57.160
Your sister?

186
00:12:57.320 --> 00:12:59.360
Do you know the first thing
about sword fighting?

187
00:12:59.520 --> 00:13:01.040
Stick 'em with the pointy end.

188
00:13:01.200 --> 00:13:02.520
(LAUGHS)

189
00:13:02.680 --> 00:13:05.040
That's the essence of it.

190
00:13:07.040 --> 00:13:08.960
I was trying to learn.

191
00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:13.720
I asked Mycah to practice with me.

192
00:13:15.280 --> 00:13:17.280
I asked him.

193
00:13:17.440 --> 00:13:20.120
-It was my fault.
-No. sweet girl.

194
00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:24.640
No. no.
you didn't kill the butcher's boy.

195
00:13:24.800 --> 00:13:27.760
I hate them! I hate all of them.

196
00:13:27.920 --> 00:13:31.600
The Hound. the queen and the king
and Joffrey and Sansa.

197
00:13:31.760 --> 00:13:35.200
Sansa was dragged
before the king and queen...

198
00:13:35.360 --> 00:13:37.760
and asked to call the prince a liar.

199
00:13:37.920 --> 00:13:40.320
So was I! He is a liar.

200
00:13:40.480 --> 00:13:43.800
Shh. darling. listen to me.

201
00:13:43.960 --> 00:13:46.960
Sansa will be married to Joffrey's
someday.

202
00:13:47.120 --> 00:13:48.920
She cannot betray him.

203
00:13:49.080 --> 00:13:52.440
She must take his side
even when he's wrong.

204
00:13:52.600 --> 00:13:55.320
But how you can let her marry
someone like that?

205
00:13:57.360 --> 00:13:58.800
Well.

206
00:14:00.880 --> 00:14:03.160
Look at me.

207
00:14:03.320 --> 00:14:06.600
You're a Stark of Winterfell.
You know our words.

208
00:14:08.680 --> 00:14:10.960
Winter is coming.

209
00:14:11.120 --> 00:14:13.120
You were born in the long summer.

210
00:14:13.280 --> 00:14:15.000
You've never known anything else.

211
00:14:15.160 --> 00:14:16.760
But now winter is truly coming.

212
00:14:16.920 --> 00:14:20.720
And in the winter.
we must protect ourselves.

213
00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:25.720
look after one another.
Sansa is your sister.

214
00:14:25.880 --> 00:14:28.480
I don't hate her.

215
00:14:28.640 --> 00:14:31.080
Not really.

216
00:14:31.240 --> 00:14:33.000
I don't want to frighten you.

217
00:14:33.160 --> 00:14:34.800
but I won't lie to you either.

218
00:14:34.960 --> 00:14:38.120
We've come to a dangerous place.

219
00:14:38.280 --> 00:14:41.560
We cannot fight a war amongst ourselves.

220
00:14:41.720 --> 00:14:44.160
All right?

221
00:14:44.320 --> 00:14:47.520
Go on. It's yours.

222
00:14:50.240 --> 00:14:52.520
I can keep it?

223
00:14:52.680 --> 00:14:56.040
Try not to stab your sister with it.
(CHUCKLES)

224
00:15:01.520 --> 00:15:03.000
(CHUCKLES)

225
00:15:03.160 --> 00:15:05.120
If you're going to own a sword.

226
00:15:05.280 --> 00:15:07.880
you'd better know how to use it.

227
00:15:09.400 --> 00:15:12.560
(CAWING)

228
00:15:14.360 --> 00:15:18.560
Don't listen to it. Crows are all liars.

229
00:15:20.160 --> 00:15:23.840
-I know a story about a crow.
-I hate your stories.

230
00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:27.880
I know a story about a boy
who hated stories.

231
00:15:28.040 --> 00:15:30.360
I could tell you
about ser Duncan the Tall.

232
00:15:30.520 --> 00:15:32.360
Those were always your favorites.

233
00:15:32.520 --> 00:15:35.040
Those weren't my favorites.

234
00:15:35.200 --> 00:15:37.040
My favorites were the scary ones.

235
00:15:38.600 --> 00:15:43.760
Oh. my sweet summer child.
What do you know about fear?

236
00:15:43.920 --> 00:15:45.600
Fear is for the winter.

237
00:15:45.760 --> 00:15:49.000
when the snows fall a hundred feet deep.

238
00:15:49.160 --> 00:15:53.280
Fear is for the long night.
when the sun hides for years

239
00:15:53.440 --> 00:15:56.400
and children are born and live and die

240
00:15:56.560 --> 00:15:58.960
all in darkness.

241
00:15:59.120 --> 00:16:01.720
That is the time for fear.
my little lord.

242
00:16:01.880 --> 00:16:06.320
when the White Walkers move
through the woods.

243
00:16:06.480 --> 00:16:09.160
Thousands of years ago
there came a night

244
00:16:09.320 --> 00:16:11.520
that lasted a generation.

245
00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:14.000
Kings froze to death in their castles.

246
00:16:14.160 --> 00:16:16.520
same as the shepherds in their huts.

247
00:16:16.680 --> 00:16:18.880
And women smothered their babies

248
00:16:19.040 --> 00:16:21.000
rather than see them starve.

249
00:16:21.160 --> 00:16:26.080
and wept and felt the tears
freeze on their cheeks.

250
00:16:26.240 --> 00:16:29.720
So is this the sort of story
that you like?

251
00:16:32.120 --> 00:16:33.440
In that darkness.

252
00:16:33.600 --> 00:16:36.160
the White Walkers came
for the first time.

253
00:16:36.320 --> 00:16:39.040
They swept through cities and kingdoms.

254
00:16:39.200 --> 00:16:41.120
riding their dead horses.

255
00:16:41.280 --> 00:16:45.000
hunting with their packs
of pale spiders big as hounds--

256
00:16:45.160 --> 00:16:47.200
(DOOR RATTLES)

257
00:16:49.800 --> 00:16:51.120
What are you telling him now?

258
00:16:51.280 --> 00:16:53.480
Only what the little lord wants to hear.

259
00:16:53.640 --> 00:16:56.360
Get your supper.
I want some time with him.

260
00:17:05.080 --> 00:17:07.240
(DOOR CLOSES)

261
00:17:07.400 --> 00:17:10.720
One time she told me the sky is blue
because we live

262
00:17:10.880 --> 00:17:13.440
inside the eye of a blue-eyed giant
named Macomber.

263
00:17:13.600 --> 00:17:15.480
Maybe we do.

264
00:17:17.960 --> 00:17:19.760
How do you feel?

265
00:17:23.840 --> 00:17:25.680
You still don't remember anything?

266
00:17:27.520 --> 00:17:29.120
Bran.

267
00:17:29.280 --> 00:17:31.200
I've seen you climb a thousand times.

268
00:17:31.360 --> 00:17:33.240
In the wind. in the rain--

269
00:17:33.400 --> 00:17:35.160
a thousand times.

270
00:17:35.320 --> 00:17:37.880
-You never fall.
-I did though.

271
00:17:40.680 --> 00:17:43.240
It's true. isn't it.

272
00:17:43.400 --> 00:17:46.440
what Maester Luwin says about my legs?

273
00:17:53.520 --> 00:17:56.120
I'd rather be dead.

274
00:17:56.280 --> 00:18:00.040
-Don't ever say that.
-I'd rather be dead.

275
00:18:10.720 --> 00:18:12.920
Fewer eyes back here. my lady.

276
00:18:13.080 --> 00:18:14.800
But still too many.

277
00:18:14.960 --> 00:18:17.560
It's nine years
since I've set foot in the capital.

278
00:18:17.720 --> 00:18:21.200
And no one knew who I was
the last time I came either.

279
00:18:24.120 --> 00:18:26.440
My lady.

280
00:18:26.600 --> 00:18:29.640
Welcome to King's Landing. Lady Stark.
Would you mind following us?

281
00:18:29.800 --> 00:18:31.440
I would. We've done nothing wrong.

282
00:18:31.600 --> 00:18:33.520
We've been instructed
to escort you into the city.

283
00:18:33.680 --> 00:18:35.320
Instructed?

284
00:18:35.480 --> 00:18:37.880
I don't know who's providing
your instructions. but--

285
00:18:38.040 --> 00:18:40.080
Follow me. Lady Stark.

286
00:18:50.320 --> 00:18:54.560
Cat! Go on. Go upstairs.

287
00:18:57.040 --> 00:18:59.840
You little worm!

288
00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:02.000
You take me for some back-alley sally

289
00:19:02.160 --> 00:19:04.440
you can drag into a--

290
00:19:09.160 --> 00:19:10.720
I meant no disrespect

291
00:19:10.880 --> 00:19:13.120
to you of all people.

292
00:19:13.280 --> 00:19:16.920
How dare you bring me here!
Have you lost your mind?

293
00:19:17.080 --> 00:19:18.960
No one will come looking for you here.
Isn't that what you wanted?

294
00:19:19.120 --> 00:19:22.880
I'm truly sorry about the locale.

295
00:19:23.040 --> 00:19:26.360
How did you know
I was coming to King's Landing?

296
00:19:26.520 --> 00:19:28.880
A dear friend told me.

297
00:19:29.880 --> 00:19:32.720
-Lady Stark.
-Lord Varys.

298
00:19:32.880 --> 00:19:36.360
To see you again
after so many years is a blessing.

299
00:19:36.520 --> 00:19:38.560
Your poor hands.

300
00:19:40.080 --> 00:19:44.440
-How did you know I was coming?
-Knowledge is my trade. my lady.

301
00:19:44.600 --> 00:19:45.920
(SCOFFS)

302
00:19:46.080 --> 00:19:49.280
Did you bring the dagger with you.
by any chance?

303
00:19:49.440 --> 00:19:51.960
My little birds are everywhere...

304
00:19:52.120 --> 00:19:54.240
even in the North.

305
00:19:54.400 --> 00:19:58.240
They whisper to me
the strangest stories.

306
00:20:03.040 --> 00:20:04.720
Valyrian steel.

307
00:20:04.880 --> 00:20:07.440
Do you know whose dagger this is?

308
00:20:08.920 --> 00:20:10.920
I must admit I do not.

309
00:20:11.080 --> 00:20:15.320
(CHUCKLES)
Well well. this is an historic day.

310
00:20:15.480 --> 00:20:18.920
Something you don't know that I do.

311
00:20:21.120 --> 00:20:24.840
There's only one dagger like this
in all of the Seven Kingdoms.

312
00:20:26.400 --> 00:20:28.800
-It's mine.
-Yours?

313
00:20:28.960 --> 00:20:33.640
At least it was. until the tournament
on prince Joffrey's last Nameday.

314
00:20:33.800 --> 00:20:35.600
I bet on ser Jaime in the jousting.

315
00:20:35.760 --> 00:20:37.280
as any sane man would.

316
00:20:37.440 --> 00:20:40.840
When the Knight of the Flowers
unseated him.

317
00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:42.520
I lost this dagger.

318
00:20:42.680 --> 00:20:44.480
To whom?

319
00:20:44.640 --> 00:20:46.280
Tyrion Lannister.

320
00:20:46.440 --> 00:20:48.520
The imp.

321
00:20:48.680 --> 00:20:51.120
MAN: Grenn. show him what you farm boys
are made of.

322
00:20:51.280 --> 00:20:54.840
(GRUNTING)

323
00:20:56.240 --> 00:20:59.400
If that were a real sword.
you'd be dead.

324
00:20:59.560 --> 00:21:02.320
Lord Snow here grew up in a castle

325
00:21:02.480 --> 00:21:04.520
spitting down on the likes of you.

326
00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:06.560
Pyp.

327
00:21:06.720 --> 00:21:08.520
Do you think Ned Stark's bastard

328
00:21:08.680 --> 00:21:10.800
bleeds like the rest of us?

329
00:21:14.160 --> 00:21:15.560
(SHOUTS. GRUNTS)

330
00:21:15.720 --> 00:21:18.200
(COUGHS)

331
00:21:18.360 --> 00:21:20.600
Next!

332
00:21:30.080 --> 00:21:31.520
Next!

333
00:21:44.240 --> 00:21:48.240
Well. Lord Snow. it appears
you're the least useless person here.

334
00:21:49.440 --> 00:21:51.200
Go clean yourselves up.

335
00:21:51.360 --> 00:21:53.760
There's only so much
I can stomach in a day.

336
00:21:53.920 --> 00:21:55.640
A charming man.

337
00:21:55.800 --> 00:21:58.000
COMMANDER: I don't need him
to be charming.

338
00:21:58.160 --> 00:22:01.360
I need him to turn
this bunch of thieves and runaways

339
00:22:01.520 --> 00:22:03.360
into men of the Night's Watch.

340
00:22:03.520 --> 00:22:05.960
And how's that going. Commander Mormont?

341
00:22:06.120 --> 00:22:07.480
Slowly.

342
00:22:09.880 --> 00:22:11.480
A raven came

343
00:22:11.640 --> 00:22:13.080
for Ned Stark's son.

344
00:22:17.200 --> 00:22:20.560
-Good news or bad?
-Both.

345
00:22:22.000 --> 00:22:23.440
MAESTER PYCELLE: Lord Stark.

346
00:22:23.600 --> 00:22:25.000
(GROANING)

347
00:22:25.160 --> 00:22:29.800
I meant to give you this earlier.
(GROANING)

348
00:22:29.960 --> 00:22:31.880
So forgetful these days.

349
00:22:33.280 --> 00:22:37.360
A raven from Winterfell this morning.

350
00:22:47.040 --> 00:22:49.400
Good news?

351
00:22:52.320 --> 00:22:55.400
Perhaps you'd like to share it
with your wife?

352
00:22:57.200 --> 00:22:59.680
-My wife is in Winterfell.
-Is she?

353
00:23:08.160 --> 00:23:12.160
WOMAN: Yes. I'm looking at you.
(LAUGHTER)

354
00:23:12.320 --> 00:23:14.840
I thought that she'd be safest in here.

355
00:23:15.000 --> 00:23:18.320
One of several such establishments
I own.

356
00:23:19.440 --> 00:23:24.560
You're a funny man.
Huh? A very funny man.

357
00:23:24.720 --> 00:23:26.920
Ned!

358
00:23:33.200 --> 00:23:35.280
Ah. the Starks--

359
00:23:35.440 --> 00:23:37.880
Quick tempers. slow minds.

360
00:23:42.800 --> 00:23:45.240
You broke my nose. bastard!

361
00:23:53.200 --> 00:23:55.600
It's an improvement.

362
00:23:57.560 --> 00:23:59.800
If we threw you over the wall. I wonder
how long it would take you to hit.

363
00:23:59.960 --> 00:24:02.160
I wonder if they'd find you
before the wolves did.

364
00:24:02.320 --> 00:24:04.120
(DOOR OPENS)

365
00:24:06.800 --> 00:24:09.440
What're you looking at. half man?

366
00:24:09.600 --> 00:24:12.160
I'm looking at you.

367
00:24:12.320 --> 00:24:13.800
Yes.

368
00:24:13.960 --> 00:24:17.280
You've got an interesting face.

369
00:24:17.440 --> 00:24:22.600
Hmm. very distinctive faces.
All of you.

370
00:24:22.760 --> 00:24:24.160
And what do you care about our faces?

371
00:24:24.320 --> 00:24:27.240
It's just I think
they would look marvelous

372
00:24:27.400 --> 00:24:29.800
decorating spikes in King's Landing.

373
00:24:29.960 --> 00:24:33.600
Perhaps I'll write my sister. the queen.
about it.

374
00:24:35.120 --> 00:24:37.360
We'll talk later. Lord Snow.

375
00:24:39.240 --> 00:24:43.160
(PANTING)

376
00:24:43.320 --> 00:24:45.440
Everybody knew what this place was

377
00:24:45.600 --> 00:24:47.200
and no one told me.

378
00:24:47.360 --> 00:24:49.240
No one but you.

379
00:24:49.400 --> 00:24:51.200
My father knew

380
00:24:51.360 --> 00:24:53.400
and he left me to rot at the wall
all the same.

381
00:24:53.560 --> 00:24:55.040
Grenn's father left him too...

382
00:24:55.200 --> 00:24:59.000
outside a farmhouse when he was three.

383
00:24:59.160 --> 00:25:02.520
Pyp was caught stealing
a wheel of cheese.

384
00:25:02.680 --> 00:25:06.200
His little sister hadn't eaten
in three days.

385
00:25:06.360 --> 00:25:09.040
He was given a choice:
his right hand or the wall.

386
00:25:09.200 --> 00:25:12.760
I've been asking the lord commander
about them. Fascinating stories.

387
00:25:12.920 --> 00:25:15.000
They hate me
because I'm better than they are.

388
00:25:15.160 --> 00:25:16.960
It's a lucky thing none of them
were trained by a master-at-arms

389
00:25:17.120 --> 00:25:19.040
like your ser Rodrik.

390
00:25:19.200 --> 00:25:21.480
I don't imagine any of them
have ever held a real sword

391
00:25:21.640 --> 00:25:23.640
before they came here.

392
00:25:26.720 --> 00:25:28.960
Oh...

393
00:25:29.120 --> 00:25:31.480
Your brother Bran.

394
00:25:31.640 --> 00:25:33.680
He's woken up.

395
00:25:35.400 --> 00:25:36.960
The mere suggestion
that the queen's brother

396
00:25:37.120 --> 00:25:39.080
tried to kill your boy
would be considered treason.

397
00:25:39.240 --> 00:25:41.400
We have proof. We have the blade.

398
00:25:41.560 --> 00:25:43.400
Which Lord Tyrion will say
was stolen from him.

399
00:25:43.560 --> 00:25:45.760
The only man who could say otherwise
has no throat.

400
00:25:45.920 --> 00:25:48.200
thanks to your boy's wolf.

401
00:25:48.360 --> 00:25:52.040
Petyr has promised
to help us find the truth.

402
00:25:52.200 --> 00:25:53.560
He's like a little brother to me. Ned.

403
00:25:53.720 --> 00:25:56.200
He would never betray my trust.

404
00:25:56.360 --> 00:25:58.760
I'll try to keep you alive.
for her sake.

405
00:25:58.920 --> 00:26:00.400
A fool's task. admittedly.

406
00:26:00.560 --> 00:26:03.160
but I've never been able
to refuse your wife anything.

407
00:26:03.320 --> 00:26:05.520
I won't forget this.

408
00:26:05.680 --> 00:26:07.320
You're a true friend.

409
00:26:07.480 --> 00:26:10.280
Don't tell anyone.
I have a reputation to maintain.

410
00:26:10.440 --> 00:26:12.240
(KNOCKS)

411
00:26:14.320 --> 00:26:16.680
-How could you be so stupid?
-Calm down.

412
00:26:16.840 --> 00:26:18.960
He's a child-- 10 years old.

413
00:26:19.120 --> 00:26:21.000
-What were you thinking?
-I was thinking of us.

414
00:26:21.160 --> 00:26:23.920
You're a bit late
to start complaining about it now.

415
00:26:24.080 --> 00:26:26.080
-What has the boy told them?
-Nothing. He's said nothing.

416
00:26:26.240 --> 00:26:29.160
-He remembers nothing.
-Then what are you raving about?

417
00:26:29.320 --> 00:26:32.520
What if it comes back to him?
If he tells his father what he saw--

418
00:26:32.680 --> 00:26:34.760
We'll say he was lying.
We'll say he was dreaming.

419
00:26:34.920 --> 00:26:36.400
We'll say whatever we like.

420
00:26:36.560 --> 00:26:38.520
I think we can outfox a 10-year-old.

421
00:26:38.680 --> 00:26:42.360
-And my husband?
-I'll go to war with him if I have to.

422
00:26:42.520 --> 00:26:44.480
They can write a ballad about us:

423
00:26:44.640 --> 00:26:46.960
"The war for Cersei's cunt."

424
00:26:48.280 --> 00:26:49.720
(CHUCKLES)

425
00:26:51.600 --> 00:26:53.600
-Let me go.
-Never.

426
00:26:53.760 --> 00:26:55.080
Let me go.

427
00:26:55.240 --> 00:26:57.880
The boy won't talk.

428
00:26:58.040 --> 00:26:59.880
And if he does. I'll kill him.

429
00:27:00.040 --> 00:27:03.160
Him. Ned Stark. the king--
the whole bloody lot of them.

430
00:27:03.320 --> 00:27:06.000
until you and I are the only people

431
00:27:06.160 --> 00:27:08.640
left in this world.

432
00:27:18.520 --> 00:27:20.480
I wish I could see the girls.

433
00:27:20.640 --> 00:27:23.480
-It's too dangerous.
-Just for a moment.

434
00:27:23.640 --> 00:27:25.520
Until we know who our enemies are--

435
00:27:25.680 --> 00:27:27.600
I know they did it. Ned. The Lannisters.

436
00:27:27.760 --> 00:27:29.600
In my bones. I know it.

437
00:27:29.760 --> 00:27:31.720
Littlefinger's right.

438
00:27:33.360 --> 00:27:35.200
I can't do anything without proof.

439
00:27:35.360 --> 00:27:37.760
And if you find the proof?

440
00:27:37.920 --> 00:27:40.400
Then I bring it to Robert...

441
00:27:40.560 --> 00:27:43.080
and hope he's still the man I once knew.

442
00:27:44.440 --> 00:27:47.280
You watch yourself on the road. huh?

443
00:27:47.440 --> 00:27:49.160
That temper of yours
is a dangerous thing.

444
00:27:49.320 --> 00:27:52.280
My temper? Gods be good.

445
00:27:52.440 --> 00:27:55.480
you nearly killed
poor Littlefinger yesterday.

446
00:27:59.640 --> 00:28:01.240
He still loves you.

447
00:28:02.520 --> 00:28:04.120
Does he?

448
00:28:21.720 --> 00:28:24.440
Off with you.

449
00:28:35.320 --> 00:28:37.240
(HORSE SNORTS)

450
00:28:53.440 --> 00:28:57.400
Yes. it's been a long time.

451
00:28:57.560 --> 00:28:59.880
But I still remember every face.

452
00:29:01.720 --> 00:29:03.720
You remember your first?

453
00:29:05.920 --> 00:29:08.000
Of course. your grace.

454
00:29:08.160 --> 00:29:10.200
Who was it?

455
00:29:10.360 --> 00:29:12.040
A Tyroshi.

456
00:29:12.200 --> 00:29:15.200
Never learned the name.
(KING SCOFFS)

457
00:29:15.360 --> 00:29:18.880
-How'd you do it?
-Lance through the heart.

458
00:29:19.040 --> 00:29:21.400
Quick one.

459
00:29:21.560 --> 00:29:24.000
Lucky for you.

460
00:29:24.160 --> 00:29:29.160
Mine was some Tarly boy
at the battle of Summerhall.

461
00:29:29.320 --> 00:29:31.480
My horse took an arrow so I was on foot.

462
00:29:31.640 --> 00:29:33.280
slogging through the mud.

463
00:29:34.880 --> 00:29:40.080
He came running at me.
this dumb high-born lad.

464
00:29:40.240 --> 00:29:44.600
thinking he could end the rebellion
with a single swing of his sword.

465
00:29:45.720 --> 00:29:47.320
I knocked him down with the hammer.

466
00:29:47.480 --> 00:29:49.840
Gods. I was strong then.

467
00:29:50.000 --> 00:29:53.320
Caved in his breastplate.

468
00:29:53.480 --> 00:29:56.600
Probably shattered every rib he had.

469
00:29:56.760 --> 00:30:00.200
Stood over him. hammer in the air.

470
00:30:00.360 --> 00:30:05.240
Right before I brought it down
he shouted. "Wait! Wait."

471
00:30:05.400 --> 00:30:07.920
(LAUGHS)

472
00:30:10.880 --> 00:30:14.520
They never tell you
how they all shit themselves.

473
00:30:16.040 --> 00:30:19.000
They don't put that part in the songs.

474
00:30:21.160 --> 00:30:23.400
Stupid boy.

475
00:30:24.760 --> 00:30:27.160
Now the Tarlys bend the knee

476
00:30:27.320 --> 00:30:29.320
like everyone else.

477
00:30:29.480 --> 00:30:31.160
He could have lingered

478
00:30:31.320 --> 00:30:33.720
on the edge of the battle
with the smart boys

479
00:30:33.880 --> 00:30:37.960
and today his wife
would be making him miserable.

480
00:30:38.120 --> 00:30:40.640
his sons would be ingrates.

481
00:30:40.800 --> 00:30:43.040
and he'd be waking
three times in the night

482
00:30:43.200 --> 00:30:46.680
to piss into a bowl. Wine!

483
00:30:49.160 --> 00:30:54.320
Lancel. Gods. what a stupid name.

484
00:30:54.480 --> 00:30:57.840
Lancel Lannister.

485
00:30:58.000 --> 00:31:01.840
Who named you?
Some halfwit with a stutter?

486
00:31:02.000 --> 00:31:04.840
(CHUCKLES)

487
00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:06.600
What are you doing?

488
00:31:08.120 --> 00:31:10.680
-It's empty. your grace.
-What do you mean it's empty?

489
00:31:10.840 --> 00:31:14.880
-There's no more wine.
-Is that what empty means?

490
00:31:15.040 --> 00:31:19.280
So get more.

491
00:31:21.800 --> 00:31:23.800
Tell your cousin to get in here.

492
00:31:23.960 --> 00:31:26.560
Kingslayer! Get in here.

493
00:31:34.040 --> 00:31:36.920
Surrounded by Lannisters.

494
00:31:37.080 --> 00:31:40.600
Every time I close my eyes
I see their blond hair

495
00:31:40.760 --> 00:31:44.760
and their smug. satisfied faces.

496
00:31:44.920 --> 00:31:46.680
It must wound your pride. huh?

497
00:31:46.840 --> 00:31:51.000
Standing out there
like a glorified sentry.

498
00:31:51.160 --> 00:31:55.880
Jaime Lannister.
son of the mighty Tywin...

499
00:31:56.040 --> 00:32:01.760
forced to mind the door while your king
eats and drinks and shits and fucks.

500
00:32:03.120 --> 00:32:04.600
So come on.

501
00:32:04.760 --> 00:32:06.760
We're telling war stories.

502
00:32:08.040 --> 00:32:11.200
Who was your first kill.
not counting old men?

503
00:32:12.880 --> 00:32:15.440
One of the outlaws in the brotherhood.

504
00:32:15.600 --> 00:32:17.640
I was there that day.

505
00:32:17.800 --> 00:32:20.920
You were only a squire. 16 years old.

506
00:32:21.080 --> 00:32:23.400
You killed Simon Toyne
with a counter riposte.

507
00:32:23.560 --> 00:32:26.360
Best move I ever saw.

508
00:32:26.520 --> 00:32:30.360
A good fighter. Toyne.
but he lacked stamina.

509
00:32:30.520 --> 00:32:34.320
Your outlaw... Any last words?

510
00:32:34.480 --> 00:32:37.560
-I cut his head off. so no.
-Hmmm.

511
00:32:37.720 --> 00:32:39.960
What about Aerys Targaryen?

512
00:32:40.120 --> 00:32:43.920
What did the Mad King say
when you stabbed him in the back?

513
00:32:44.080 --> 00:32:46.320
I never asked.

514
00:32:46.480 --> 00:32:48.680
Did he call you a traitor?

515
00:32:48.840 --> 00:32:51.600
Did he plead for a reprieve?

516
00:32:53.400 --> 00:32:56.280
He said the same thing
he'd been saying for hours...

517
00:32:57.760 --> 00:33:00.160
"Burn them all."

518
00:33:04.360 --> 00:33:06.160
If that's all. your grace...

519
00:33:11.160 --> 00:33:14.840
(DRUMS BEATING)

520
00:33:37.360 --> 00:33:39.560
Do the Dothraki buy their slaves?

521
00:33:39.720 --> 00:33:41.520
The Dothraki don't believe in money.

522
00:33:41.680 --> 00:33:43.760
Most of their slaves were given to them
as gifts.

523
00:33:43.920 --> 00:33:46.240
-From whom?
-If you rule a city

524
00:33:46.400 --> 00:33:48.720
and you see the horde approaching.
you have two choices:

525
00:33:48.880 --> 00:33:50.680
pay tribute or fight.

526
00:33:50.840 --> 00:33:53.600
An easy choice for most.

527
00:33:53.760 --> 00:33:55.880
Of course. sometimes it's not enough.

528
00:33:56.040 --> 00:33:59.160
Sometimes a Khal feels insulted
by the number of slaves he's given.

529
00:33:59.320 --> 00:34:02.200
He might think the men too weak
or the women too ugly.

530
00:34:02.360 --> 00:34:05.240
Sometimes a Khal decides his riders
haven't had a good fight in months

531
00:34:05.400 --> 00:34:06.840
and need the practice.

532
00:34:07.000 --> 00:34:11.160
Kash qoy qoyi thira disse.
(SLAVE WHIMPERING. WHIP CRACKING)

533
00:34:11.320 --> 00:34:13.080
Tell them all to stop.

534
00:34:13.240 --> 00:34:15.160
You want the entire horde to stop?

535
00:34:15.320 --> 00:34:17.640
For how long?

536
00:34:17.800 --> 00:34:20.360
Until I command them otherwise.

537
00:34:20.520 --> 00:34:22.640
You're learning to talk like a queen.

538
00:34:22.800 --> 00:34:25.360
Not a queen.

539
00:34:25.520 --> 00:34:28.120
A Khaleesi.

540
00:34:56.200 --> 00:34:59.920
(BRANCHES RUSTLING)

541
00:35:00.080 --> 00:35:01.880
(BLADE CLANGING)

542
00:35:02.040 --> 00:35:03.960
(HORSE NEIGHS)
You dare!

543
00:35:04.120 --> 00:35:07.560
You give commands to me? To me?

544
00:35:09.160 --> 00:35:12.680
You do not command the dragon.
I am lord of the Seven Kingdoms.

545
00:35:12.840 --> 00:35:15.840
I don't take orders from savages
or their sluts.

546
00:35:16.000 --> 00:35:17.760
Do you hear me?

547
00:35:20.120 --> 00:35:22.400
Hash shafka zali nharees. zhey khaleesi?

548
00:35:22.560 --> 00:35:24.840
Rakharo ask if you want him dead.
Khaleesi.

549
00:35:25.000 --> 00:35:26.600
No.

550
00:35:26.760 --> 00:35:29.760
Ishish chare acharoe hash me nem ajervae
nharesoon.

551
00:35:29.920 --> 00:35:32.360
Rakharo say you should take ear.
to teach respect.

552
00:35:32.520 --> 00:35:35.520
Please. please. don't hurt him.

553
00:35:39.280 --> 00:35:43.120
Tell him I don't want my brother harmed.

554
00:35:43.280 --> 00:35:45.240
Khaleesi vos zalo meme nem azisa.

555
00:35:45.400 --> 00:35:47.360
Huh?

556
00:35:48.400 --> 00:35:52.120
Shafki.
(GASPING)

557
00:35:55.000 --> 00:35:58.080
Mormont! Kill these Dothraki dogs!

558
00:36:03.360 --> 00:36:07.200
I am your king!

559
00:36:07.360 --> 00:36:10.680
Shall we return to the khalasar.
Khaleesi?

560
00:36:29.440 --> 00:36:31.160
Uh uh uh uh uh.

561
00:36:31.320 --> 00:36:34.800
You walk.

562
00:36:36.280 --> 00:36:38.680
(CLICKS TONGUE)

563
00:36:42.640 --> 00:36:45.080
(WIND WHISPERING)

564
00:37:09.920 --> 00:37:12.600
(METAL CLANGS)

565
00:37:49.960 --> 00:37:54.120
(CREAKING)

566
00:38:00.880 --> 00:38:03.280
(BELL DINGS)

567
00:38:16.360 --> 00:38:20.840
(WIND ROARING)

568
00:38:58.480 --> 00:39:03.640
BENJEN: I wanted to be here
when you saw it for the first time.

569
00:39:10.360 --> 00:39:13.320
-I'm leaving this morning.
-You're leaving?

570
00:39:14.680 --> 00:39:16.640
I'm the First Ranger.

571
00:39:16.800 --> 00:39:18.920
My job is out there.

572
00:39:19.080 --> 00:39:22.520
-There have been disturbing reports.
-What kind of reports?

573
00:39:22.680 --> 00:39:25.320
The kind I don't want to believe.

574
00:39:25.480 --> 00:39:28.680
I'm ready. I won't let you down.

575
00:39:28.840 --> 00:39:31.040
You're not going.

576
00:39:32.880 --> 00:39:34.640
You're no ranger. Jon.

577
00:39:34.800 --> 00:39:37.320
-But I'm better than every--
-Better than no one!

578
00:39:42.240 --> 00:39:43.920
Here...

579
00:39:44.080 --> 00:39:46.480
a man gets what he earns.

580
00:39:46.640 --> 00:39:48.560
when he earns it.

581
00:39:52.600 --> 00:39:54.640
We'll speak when I return.

582
00:39:56.400 --> 00:39:58.840
(WIND HOWLING)

583
00:40:09.120 --> 00:40:11.640
-A bear's balls.
-TYRION: Oh. you're joking?

584
00:40:11.800 --> 00:40:15.680
And his brains and his guts.
his lungs and his heart.

585
00:40:15.840 --> 00:40:17.760
all fried in his own fat.

586
00:40:17.920 --> 00:40:20.400
Well. when you're a hundred miles
north of the wall

587
00:40:20.560 --> 00:40:23.840
and you ate your last meal a week ago.
you leave nothing for the wolves.

588
00:40:24.000 --> 00:40:27.400
And how do a bear's balls taste?

589
00:40:27.560 --> 00:40:31.240
A bit chewy.
(LAUGHS)

590
00:40:31.400 --> 00:40:35.240
And what about you. my lord?
What's the strangest thing you've eaten?

591
00:40:35.400 --> 00:40:40.640
Do Dornish girls count?
(LAUGHING)

592
00:40:40.800 --> 00:40:43.800
So you roam the Seven Kingdoms.

593
00:40:43.960 --> 00:40:46.120
collaring pickpockets and horse thieves

594
00:40:46.280 --> 00:40:47.920
and bringing them here
as eager recruits?

595
00:40:48.080 --> 00:40:49.400
Aye.

596
00:40:49.560 --> 00:40:52.440
But it's not all of 'em's done
bad things.

597
00:40:52.600 --> 00:40:55.520
Some of 'em's just poor lads
looking for steady feed.

598
00:40:55.680 --> 00:40:58.280
Some of 'em's high-born lads
looking for glory.

599
00:40:58.440 --> 00:41:01.600
They have a better chance
finding feed than glory.

600
00:41:03.000 --> 00:41:06.000
The Night's Watch is a joke to you.
is it?

601
00:41:06.160 --> 00:41:08.240
Is that what we are. Lannister?

602
00:41:08.400 --> 00:41:10.240
An army of jesters in black?

603
00:41:10.400 --> 00:41:12.080
You don't have enough men to be an army

604
00:41:12.240 --> 00:41:15.880
and aside from Yoren here.
none of you are particularly funny.

605
00:41:16.040 --> 00:41:18.600
I hope we've provided you
with some good stories to tell

606
00:41:18.760 --> 00:41:20.480
when you're back in King's Landing.

607
00:41:20.640 --> 00:41:24.040
But something to think about while
you're drinking your wine down there.

608
00:41:24.200 --> 00:41:26.920
enjoying your brothels--

609
00:41:27.080 --> 00:41:30.920
Half the boys you've seen training
will die north of the wall.

610
00:41:31.080 --> 00:41:33.640
Might be a Wilding's ax that gets them.

611
00:41:33.800 --> 00:41:35.920
might be sickness.

612
00:41:36.080 --> 00:41:39.120
might just be the cold.

613
00:41:39.280 --> 00:41:41.560
They die in pain.

614
00:41:41.720 --> 00:41:44.720
And they do it
so plump little lords like you

615
00:41:44.880 --> 00:41:48.720
can enjoy their summer afternoons
in peace and comfort.

616
00:41:50.920 --> 00:41:53.400
Do you think I'm plump?

617
00:41:56.200 --> 00:41:59.120
-Listen. Benjen-- may I call you Benjen?
-Call me what you like.

618
00:41:59.280 --> 00:42:01.400
I'm not sure
what I've done to offend you.

619
00:42:01.560 --> 00:42:03.440
I have great admiration
for the Night's Watch.

620
00:42:03.600 --> 00:42:05.560
I've great admiration
for you as First Ranger.

621
00:42:05.720 --> 00:42:07.960
You know. my brother once told me

622
00:42:08.120 --> 00:42:12.960
that nothing someone says
before the word "but" really counts.

623
00:42:13.120 --> 00:42:15.240
But...

624
00:42:15.400 --> 00:42:18.400
I don't believe that giants and ghouls
and White Walkers

625
00:42:18.560 --> 00:42:20.440
are lurking beyond the wall.

626
00:42:20.600 --> 00:42:23.480
I believe that the only difference
between us and the Wildlings

627
00:42:23.640 --> 00:42:26.640
is that when the wall went up.
our ancestors happened to live

628
00:42:26.800 --> 00:42:28.920
on the right side of it.

629
00:42:29.080 --> 00:42:30.400
You're right.

630
00:42:32.640 --> 00:42:35.000
The Wildlings are no different from us.

631
00:42:35.160 --> 00:42:36.880
A little rougher maybe.

632
00:42:37.040 --> 00:42:39.560
But they're made of meat and bone.

633
00:42:39.720 --> 00:42:42.800
I know how to track them
and I know how to kill them.

634
00:42:42.960 --> 00:42:46.960
It's not the Wildlings
giving me sleepless nights.

635
00:42:47.120 --> 00:42:48.880
You've never been north of the wall.

636
00:42:49.040 --> 00:42:52.200
so don't tell me what's out there.

637
00:42:54.880 --> 00:42:56.760
Are you going below?

638
00:42:58.200 --> 00:43:00.920
-Keep well. keep warm.
-Enjoy the capital. brother.

639
00:43:01.080 --> 00:43:03.680
Oh. I always do.

640
00:43:12.040 --> 00:43:13.960
I think he's starting to like me.

641
00:43:14.120 --> 00:43:16.600
(LAUGHING)

642
00:43:17.640 --> 00:43:20.440
-"Going below"?
-Aye.

643
00:43:20.600 --> 00:43:23.640
Into the tunnel and out the other side.

644
00:43:23.800 --> 00:43:26.760
He'll be north of the wall
for a month or two.

645
00:43:28.520 --> 00:43:31.360
So you're heading
down to King's Landing too.

646
00:43:31.520 --> 00:43:34.680
Aye. day after tomorrow.

647
00:43:34.840 --> 00:43:37.920
I get about half of my recruits
from their dungeons.

648
00:43:38.080 --> 00:43:42.160
Let's share the road.
I could use some decent company.

649
00:43:42.320 --> 00:43:46.400
I... I travel a bit on the grubby side.
my lord.

650
00:43:46.560 --> 00:43:50.480
Not this time. We'll be staying
at the finest castles and inns.

651
00:43:50.640 --> 00:43:52.920
No one turns away a Lannister.

652
00:43:58.680 --> 00:44:00.560
At jakar?

653
00:44:00.720 --> 00:44:02.400
Athjahakar.

654
00:44:02.560 --> 00:44:04.800
Ath ja haker.

655
00:44:04.960 --> 00:44:06.280
Athjahakar.

656
00:44:06.440 --> 00:44:08.040
Athjahakar.

657
00:44:08.200 --> 00:44:10.240
Yes. Khaleesi.

658
00:44:11.760 --> 00:44:14.000
Oh. what are you doing?

659
00:44:14.160 --> 00:44:16.440
When was last time you bleed. Khaleesi?

660
00:44:18.720 --> 00:44:20.640
You change. Khaleesi.

661
00:44:22.080 --> 00:44:25.760
(SPEAKS DOTHRAKI)

662
00:44:28.800 --> 00:44:30.240
JORAH: For a man on horseback.

663
00:44:30.400 --> 00:44:35.240
the curved blade is a good thing.
easier to handle.

664
00:44:35.400 --> 00:44:38.800
It's a good weapon for a Dothrakan.

665
00:44:38.960 --> 00:44:42.880
But a man in full plate--
Shori tawakof

666
00:44:43.040 --> 00:44:45.200
The arakh won't get through the steel.

667
00:44:46.360 --> 00:44:48.680
That's where the broadsword
has the advantage.

668
00:44:48.840 --> 00:44:51.560
Designed for piercing plate.

669
00:44:52.800 --> 00:44:55.400
(SPEAKS DOTHRAKI)

670
00:44:55.560 --> 00:44:58.280
-Armor.
-Armor.

671
00:44:58.440 --> 00:45:01.240
Armor make a man...

672
00:45:01.400 --> 00:45:02.880
-Vroz?
-Slow.

673
00:45:03.040 --> 00:45:04.840
-Slow.
-It's true.

674
00:45:05.000 --> 00:45:07.800
but it also keeps a man alive.

675
00:45:07.960 --> 00:45:11.240
(SPEAKS DOTHRAKI)

676
00:45:25.880 --> 00:45:28.160
He still is.

677
00:45:28.320 --> 00:45:30.680
A man of great honor

678
00:45:30.840 --> 00:45:32.800
and I betrayed him.

679
00:45:36.960 --> 00:45:38.800
(SPEAKS DOTHRAKI)

680
00:45:55.120 --> 00:45:57.400
I don't think she wants to eat dog.

681
00:46:00.480 --> 00:46:02.600
The Khaleesi have baby inside her.

682
00:46:04.280 --> 00:46:08.040
It is true. She does not bleed
for two moons.

683
00:46:08.200 --> 00:46:10.400
Her belly start to swell.

684
00:46:11.480 --> 00:46:13.680
(RAKHARO SPEAKS DOTHRAKI)

685
00:46:13.840 --> 00:46:16.680
She does not want to eat horse.

686
00:46:16.840 --> 00:46:19.320
I'll have the boys butcher a goat
for supper.

687
00:46:22.200 --> 00:46:24.840
(MUTTERS)

688
00:46:25.000 --> 00:46:27.560
I need to ride to Qohor.

689
00:46:29.800 --> 00:46:33.640
Uh. we ride for Vaes Dothrak.

690
00:46:33.800 --> 00:46:36.160
Don't worry. I'll catch you.

691
00:46:36.320 --> 00:46:38.280
The horde's easy to find.

692
00:46:38.440 --> 00:46:40.760
(GRUNTS. SWORDS CLASH)

693
00:46:49.320 --> 00:46:51.200
Don't stand so still.

694
00:46:51.360 --> 00:46:53.680
It's harder to hit a moving target.

695
00:46:57.640 --> 00:47:00.320
Except for you. You move too much.

696
00:47:00.480 --> 00:47:02.760
I could just hold my sword out
and let you do the work for me.

697
00:47:08.280 --> 00:47:11.200
MAESTER AEMON: How many winters
have you seen. Lord Tyrion?

698
00:47:11.360 --> 00:47:15.120
-Eight-- no. nine.
-All of them brief?

699
00:47:15.280 --> 00:47:18.880
They say the winter of my birth
was three years long. Maester Aemon.

700
00:47:19.040 --> 00:47:22.600
This summer has lasted nine.

701
00:47:22.760 --> 00:47:26.200
But reports from the citadel tell us
the days grow shorter.

702
00:47:26.360 --> 00:47:28.360
The Starks are always right eventually:

703
00:47:28.520 --> 00:47:31.720
winter is coming.

704
00:47:31.880 --> 00:47:34.440
This one will be long

705
00:47:34.600 --> 00:47:36.960
and dark things will come with it.

706
00:47:37.120 --> 00:47:39.440
We've been capturing Wildlings.

707
00:47:39.600 --> 00:47:42.560
more every month. They're fleeing south.

708
00:47:42.720 --> 00:47:46.440
The ones who flee
say they've seen the White Walkers.

709
00:47:46.600 --> 00:47:50.240
Yes. and the fishermen of Lannisport
say they see mermaids.

710
00:47:50.400 --> 00:47:53.680
One of our own rangers swore
he saw them kill his companions.

711
00:47:53.840 --> 00:47:55.480
He swore it right up to the moment

712
00:47:55.640 --> 00:47:57.880
Ned Stark chopped his head off.

713
00:47:58.040 --> 00:48:00.120
The Night's Watch is the only thing

714
00:48:00.280 --> 00:48:01.800
standing between the realm

715
00:48:01.960 --> 00:48:03.920
and what lies beyond.

716
00:48:04.080 --> 00:48:05.720
And it has has become an army

717
00:48:05.880 --> 00:48:09.800
of undisciplined boys and tired old men.

718
00:48:09.960 --> 00:48:12.920
There are
less than a thousand of us now.

719
00:48:13.080 --> 00:48:15.720
We can't man
the other castles on the wall.

720
00:48:15.880 --> 00:48:18.680
We can't properly patrol the wilderness.

721
00:48:18.840 --> 00:48:23.080
We've barely enough resources
to keep our lads armed and fed.

722
00:48:23.240 --> 00:48:28.360
Your sister sits by the side the king.

723
00:48:28.520 --> 00:48:31.200
Tell her we need help.

724
00:48:31.360 --> 00:48:33.120
When winter does come.

725
00:48:33.280 --> 00:48:36.560
gods help us all if we're not ready.

726
00:48:57.600 --> 00:49:00.320
(SPEAKING DOTHRAKI)

727
00:49:22.960 --> 00:49:25.200
(WIND BLOWING)

728
00:49:40.000 --> 00:49:42.280
I'm sorry to see you leave. Lannister.

729
00:49:44.160 --> 00:49:48.080
It's either me or this cold. And
it doesn't appear to be going anywhere.

730
00:49:48.240 --> 00:49:50.880
Will you stop at Winterfell
on your way south?

731
00:49:51.040 --> 00:49:54.040
I expect I will.
Gods know there aren't many feather beds

732
00:49:54.200 --> 00:49:56.200
between here and King's Landing.

733
00:49:56.360 --> 00:49:59.240
If you see my brother Bran.

734
00:49:59.400 --> 00:50:01.680
tell him I miss him.

735
00:50:01.840 --> 00:50:04.240
-Tell him I'd visit if I could.
-Of course.

736
00:50:05.400 --> 00:50:06.760
He'll never walk again.

737
00:50:06.920 --> 00:50:10.560
If you're going to be a cripple.
it's better to be a rich cripple.

738
00:50:12.080 --> 00:50:15.920
-You take care. Snow.
-Farewell. my lord.

739
00:50:26.320 --> 00:50:28.560
(FOREIGN ACCENT)
You are late. boy.

740
00:50:30.640 --> 00:50:33.120
Tomorrow you will be here at midday.

741
00:50:33.280 --> 00:50:35.640
Who are you?

742
00:50:35.800 --> 00:50:38.800
Your dancing master. Syrio Forel.

743
00:50:43.000 --> 00:50:46.680
Tomorrow you will catch it.
Now pick it up.

744
00:50:48.560 --> 00:50:50.840
That is not the way. boy.

745
00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:54.760
This is not a great sword
that is needing two hands to swing it.

746
00:50:54.920 --> 00:50:58.720
-It's too heavy.
-It is heavy as it needs to be

747
00:50:58.880 --> 00:51:00.400
to make you strong.

748
00:51:01.600 --> 00:51:03.320
Just so.

749
00:51:03.480 --> 00:51:05.360
One hand is all that is needed.

750
00:51:07.080 --> 00:51:08.400
Now you are standing all wrong.

751
00:51:08.560 --> 00:51:10.760
Turn your body sideface.

752
00:51:10.920 --> 00:51:13.440
Yes.

753
00:51:13.600 --> 00:51:15.280
So.

754
00:51:15.440 --> 00:51:18.160
You are skinny. That is good.

755
00:51:18.320 --> 00:51:20.520
The target is smaller.

756
00:51:20.680 --> 00:51:22.440
Now the grip-- let me see.

757
00:51:23.800 --> 00:51:25.160
Yes.

758
00:51:25.320 --> 00:51:28.800
The grip must be delicate.

759
00:51:28.960 --> 00:51:30.560
What if I drop it?

760
00:51:30.720 --> 00:51:33.000
The steel must be part of your arm.

761
00:51:33.160 --> 00:51:35.640
Can you drop part of your arm? No.

762
00:51:35.800 --> 00:51:39.920
Nine years Syrio Forel was first sword
to the Sealord of Braavos.

763
00:51:40.080 --> 00:51:43.120
He knows these things.
You must listen to me. boy.

764
00:51:43.280 --> 00:51:47.960
-I'm a girl.
-Boy. girl-- you are a sword.

765
00:51:48.120 --> 00:51:50.640
that is all.
(TSKING)

766
00:51:50.800 --> 00:51:53.040
That is the grip.

767
00:51:53.200 --> 00:51:55.680
You are not holding a battle-ax.
You are holding--

768
00:51:55.840 --> 00:51:58.560
-A needle.
-Ahhh.

769
00:51:58.720 --> 00:52:00.400
(CHUCKLES)

770
00:52:00.560 --> 00:52:02.160
Just so.

771
00:52:02.320 --> 00:52:04.800
Now we will begin the dance.

772
00:52:04.960 --> 00:52:06.960
Remember. child.

773
00:52:07.120 --> 00:52:09.240
this is not the dance of the Westeros
we are learning--

774
00:52:09.400 --> 00:52:11.320
The knight's dance.

775
00:52:11.480 --> 00:52:13.640
hacking and hammering.

776
00:52:13.800 --> 00:52:18.080
This is the Braavos' dance...

777
00:52:18.240 --> 00:52:24.280
The water dance.
It is swift and sudden.

778
00:52:26.000 --> 00:52:27.880
All men are made of water.

779
00:52:28.040 --> 00:52:30.160
do you know this?

780
00:52:30.320 --> 00:52:32.320
If you pierce them.

781
00:52:32.480 --> 00:52:37.200
the water leaks out and they die.

782
00:52:37.360 --> 00:52:40.320
Now you will try to strike me.

783
00:52:40.480 --> 00:52:42.760
(SWORD THUNKS)

784
00:52:42.920 --> 00:52:45.480
Ha!

785
00:52:56.240 --> 00:52:58.200
Up!

786
00:52:58.360 --> 00:53:00.680
(TSKING)

787
00:53:00.840 --> 00:53:02.440
Ha!

788
00:53:12.440 --> 00:53:14.480
Ah.

789
00:53:16.080 --> 00:53:18.560
Dead.
(LAUGHS)

790
00:53:18.720 --> 00:53:20.200
Dead.

791
00:53:20.360 --> 00:53:22.320
(SWORDS CRASHING)
Hup!

792
00:53:24.560 --> 00:53:26.520
Very dead.

793
00:53:26.680 --> 00:53:28.240
(SOFT CHUCKLE)
SYRIO: Come.

794
00:53:28.400 --> 00:53:31.000
Ah ah ah!

795
00:53:31.160 --> 00:53:34.280
Hup!
(SWORDS CRASH)

796
00:53:34.440 --> 00:53:36.120
Again. faster.

797
00:53:40.560 --> 00:53:42.360
Ah.

798
00:53:42.520 --> 00:53:45.720
(METAL WEAPONS CLANGING.
WARRIORS SHOUTING)
